{{Notability|date=June 2011}} {{Infobox ethnic group | group = Pakistanis in Switzerland | image = | langs = [[Urdu]]{{·}} [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]]{{·}} [[English language|English]]{{·}} [[French language|French]] / [[German language|German]] / [[Italian language|Italian]]{{·}} [[Languages of Pakistan|others]] | population = 3,000 (''2004'') | popplace = [[Zürich]]{{·}} [[Bern]] | rels = [[Islam]] | related = [[Overseas Pakistani]] }}
'''Pakistanis in Switzerland''' consist of migrants from [[Pakistan]] to [[Switzerland]] and their descendants. As of 2004, there were 3,000 Pakistani nationals living in the country.<ref>[http://www.opf.org.pk/download/anual/YEARBK.pdf Yearbook 2004-2005: Overseas Pakistanis Foundation] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100524170403/http://www.opf.org.pk/download/anual/YEARBK.pdf |date=2010-05-24 }}</ref> The community is one of the largest among [[Islam in Switzerland|Muslims in Switzerland]]. Many Pakistani expatriates entered the country as political asylum seekers.<ref>[http://www.chowk.com/articles/11316 Meeting the Pakistani-Swiss: Chowk Travel] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100702140636/http://www.chowk.com/articles/11316 |date=2010-07-02 }}</ref> They are concentrated predominately in [[Zürich]] and [[Bern]]. There are a small number of Pakistani scientists working at [[CERN]].<ref>[http://cerncourier.com/cws/article/cern/28934 CERN and Pakistan: A Personal Perspective (CERN Courier)]</ref><ref>[http://cdsweb.cern.ch/record/928713 CERN and Pakistan consolidate their partnership: CERN DS]</ref>
In addition, Pakistan maintains an important diplomatic presence in Switzerland through its embassy as well as a Permanent Mission to the United Nations in [[Geneva]]. There is a ''Swiss Pakistan Society'', a non-political and non-denominational organisation of Pakistani nationals living in Switzerland.
The small [[Ahmadiyya in Switzerland|Ahmadiyya movement in Switzerland]] was initially established and run by founders from Pakistan. There are a number of Pakistanis working as high-tech experts in information technology and the health sector. In 2008, while discussing the launch of the Swiss art and film festival in [[Karachi]], the Swiss ambassador to Pakistan praised the contributions of the community and conversed on extending more opportunities in the future.<ref>[http://www.daily.pk/swiss-art-and-film-festival-on-its-way-to-karachi-5425/ Swiss art and film festival on its way to Karachi: Pakistan Daily] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120322161154/http://www.daily.pk/swiss-art-and-film-festival-on-its-way-to-karachi-5425/ |date=2012-03-22 }}</ref>
